EC2 High Availability & Scalability - Manual Console Steps
Lab 1: Create Launch Template (Console)
Step 1: Create Launch Template
Go to EC2 Console → Launch Templates
Click "Create launch template"
Configure Template:
Name: cloudops-template
Description: CloudOps web server template
AMI: Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS (latest)
Instance type: t3.micro
Key pair: demouserNvirginia
Security groups: Select existing web server security group
Advanced details → User data:
#!/bin/bash
apt update -y
apt install -y apache2
systemctl start apache2
systemctl enable apache2
echo "<h1>CloudOps Web Server - $(hostname)</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
echo "<p>Instance ID: $(curl -s http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/instance-id)</p>" >> /var/www/html/index.html
chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/html
Click "Create launch template"
Lab 2: Create Auto Scaling Group (Console)
Step 1: Create Auto Scaling Group
Go to EC2 Console → Auto Scaling Groups
Click "Create Auto Scaling group"
Choose launch template:
Name: cloudops-asg
Launch template: Select cloudops-template
Version: Latest
Click "Next"
Step 2: Configure Network
VPC: Select default VPC
Availability Zones and subnets: Select 2-3 public subnets in different AZs
Click "Next"
Step 3: Configure Advanced Options
Load balancing: Enable Application Load Balancer
Target groups: Create new target group
Name: cloudops-tg
Protocol: HTTP
Port: 80
Health checks:
Type: ELB
Grace period: 300 seconds
Click "Next"
Step 4: Configure Group Size
Desired capacity: 2
Minimum capacity: 1
Maximum capacity: 6
Scaling policies: Target tracking scaling policy
Metric type: Average CPU Utilization
Target value: 70%
Click "Next"
Step 5: Add Tags
Add tag:
Key: Name
Value: CloudOps-ASG-Instance
Click "Next" → Create Auto Scaling group
Lab 3: Create Application Load Balancer (Console)
Step 1: Create Load Balancer
Go to EC2 Console → Load Balancers
Click "Create Load Balancer"
Select "Application Load Balancer"
Step 2: Configure Load Balancer
Basic configuration:
Name: cloudops-alb
Scheme: Internet-facing
IP address type: IPv4
Network mapping:
VPC: Default VPC
Mappings: Select 2-3 availability zones
Security groups: Create or select web security group (HTTP/HTTPS)
Step 3: Configure Listeners and Routing
Listeners:
Protocol: HTTP
Port: 80
Default action: Forward to target group
Target group: Select cloudops-tg (created with ASG)
Step 4: Review and Create
Review configuration
Click "Create load balancer"
